 Jackson Township siblings are among youngest Mensa members\". Canton Rep|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> She has also competed in the 2019 Scripps National Spelling Bee.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://secure.spellingbee.com/public/results/2019/round_results/speller/468|title=2019 Scripps National Spelling Bee Round by Round Results|date=|work=|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=Word Whiz Kids Tap Memory Tricks at Spelling Bee|url=https://www.voanews.com/arts-culture/word-whiz-kids-tap-memory-tricks-spelling-bee|journal=|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vukoti, Akash}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Akash Vukoti\n| image              = Akash_Vukoti.jpg\n| caption            = Akash Vukoti in 2017\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|2009|05|29}}\n| birth_place        = [[Rockville, Maryland]], U.S.\n| nationality        = American\n| years_active       = 2012\u2013present\n| website            = {{URL|AkashVukoti.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Akash Vukoti''' is an American spelling prodigy and TV personality. He was the first-ever first grader to qualify for and compete in the [[Scripps National Spelling Bee]], and first appeared in the [[NBC]] TV show ''[[Little Big Shots]]'' in March 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2016/05/25/6-year-old-texan-misspells-word-ending-his-spelling-bee-competition/84923350/|title=6-year-old Texan misspells word, ending his spelling bee competition|last=Sullivan|first=Bartholomew|date=May 25, 2016|website=USA TODAY|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2016/05/25/6-year-old-texan-misspells-word-ending-his-spelling-bee-competition/84923350/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-moms/news/meet-the-spelling-bees-youngest-contestant-akash-vukoti-w208029/|title=Scripps National Spelling Bee\u2019s Youngest Contestant Akash Vukoti Was Too C-U-T-E: See Him in Action|last=French|first=Megan|date=May 26, 2016|website=US Magazine|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-moms/news/meet-the-spelling-bees-youngest-contestant-akash-vukoti-w208029/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/akash-vukoti-is-a-6-year-old-genius-2016-3|title=Meet the 6-year-old genius who will steal the show at this year's national spelling bee|last=Weller|first=Chris|date=March 30, 2016|website=Business Insider|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://www.businessinsider.com/akash-vukoti-is-a-6-year-old-genius-2016-3}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/national-spelling-bee-star-2016-akash-vukoti|title=This Six-Year-Old Was the First Star of the 2016 National Spelling Bee|last=Moore|first=Jack|date=May 26, 2016|website=GQ|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://www.gq.com/story/national-spelling-bee-star-2016-akash-vukoti}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=|first=|title=Why 6-Year-Old Spelling Bee Whiz Akash Vukoti Became a Global Sensation - POPSUGAR|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cvZCFRoGVUU|volume=|pages=|language=en|access-date=2019-12-08}}</ref>\n\n== Academic Achievements ==\nAkash competed in his first spelling bee when he was 2 years old.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mastispell.com/2012Champions.html|title=MastiSpell|last=|first=|date=|website=MastiSpell 2012|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\u00a0 He was inducted into [[Mensa International|American Mensa]] at the age of 3 and became a Davidson Young Scholar at the age of 5.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cantonrep.com/article/20150331/NEWS/150339817|title=G-E-N-I-U-S: Jackson Township siblings are among youngest Mensa members|last=Weir|first=Kelli|website=The Repository|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> Akash became the first-ever first grader to compete in the history of the Scripps National Spelling Bee at the age of 6 years, in [[89th Scripps National Spelling Bee|2016]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/inviscate-and-conestoga-get-two-contestants-to-the-next-round-of-the-spelling-bee/2016/05/25/d32f19ee-2272-11e6-8690-f14ca9de2972_story.html|title=\"A 6-year-old charms the National Spelling Bee before getting eliminated\".|last=Shapira|first=Ian|date=|website=Washington Post.|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Farrington|first=Dana|date=|title=\"6-Year-Old May Be Out Of Spelling Bee, But This Kid Is A Winner\". NPR.|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/05/25/479537500/6-year-old-may-be-out-of-spelling-bee-but-this-kid-is-a-winner|journal=NPR|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gosanangelo.com/story/news/2019/03/10/vukoti-wins-san-angelo-spelling-bee/3123069002/|title=Vukoti wins San Angelo Area Spelling Bee|website=San Angelo|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Gaitan|first=Michelle|date=|title=San Angelo Spelling Bee names new winner|url=http://archive.gosanangelo.com/news/local/san-angelo-spelling-bee-names-new-winner--2d3a362b-3d32-3f7b-e053-0100007fb1fb-371169381.html/|journal=|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref> Akash later competed in the [[91st Scripps National Spelling Bee|2018]] and [[92nd Scripps National Spelling Bee|2019 Scripps National Spelling Bees]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/tv/a20748354/scripps-national-spelling-bee-espn/|title=The Kids Are A-L-R-I-G-H-T: Inside the Journey to Scripps' National Spelling Bee|last=Kirkl|first=Justin|date=2018-05-31|website=Esquire|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=NUCKOLS|first=BEN|date=|title=Speller balances bee with reality TV, social media stardom|url=https://apnews.com/839b8d78fd7348029f03da2c4e15552f|journal=|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref>\n\n== TV shows ==\nAkash was featured on several TV shows<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm10071668/|title=Akash Vukoti|website=IMDb|access-date=2019-12-08}}</ref>, such as ''[[Little Big Shots]]'' in Season 1 (2016), Season 2 (2017)  and ''[[Little Big Shots (British TV series)|Little Big Shots UK]]'' (Episode 4) in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.conchovalleyhomepage.com/news/news-connection/spelling-bee-whiz-akash-vukoti-returns-to-little-big-shots/696742155|title=Spelling Bee Whiz Akash Vukoti Returns to Little Big Shots|last=Barrett|first=Daija|date=April 21, 2017|website=ConchoValley Homepage|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://www.conchovalleyhomepage.com/news/news-connection/spelling-bee-whiz-akash-vukoti-returns-to-little-big-shots/696742155}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/steve-harvey-schools-spelling-bee-champ-words-hood-074456530.html|title=Steve Harvey Schools Spelling Bee Champ on \u2018Words From the Hood\u2019|last=Paschal|first=Nick|date=April 24, 2017|website=Yahoo|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/steve-harvey-schools-spelling-bee-champ-words-hood-074456530.html}}</ref> He was also featured on the ''[[Steve Harvey (talk show)|Steve Harvey]]'' talk show,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gosanangelo.com/story/news/local/2016/03/12/precocious-local-speller-drawing-national-attention-studying-hard/92120958/|title=Precocious local speller drawing national attention, studying hard|last=|first=|date=March 12, 2016|website=gosanangelo.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://www.gosanangelo.com/story/news/local/2016/03/12/precocious-local-speller-drawing-national-attention-studying-hard/92120958/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/lifestyle/viral-and-trending/020517/w-o-n-d-e-r-kid.html|title=W-o-n-d-e-r kid|last=Gowra|first=Nikhita|date=2017-05-02|website=Deccan Chronicle|language=en|access-date=2019-12-08}}</ref> ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]],''<ref>{{Citation|title=13th Annual Jimmy Kimmel Live Spelling Bee|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZvkUCzHRo2I|language=en|access-date=2019-12-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jimmy-kimmel-spelling-bee-competition-899263|title=Jimmy Kimmel's Spelling Bee Competition Is Extra Challenging, Thanks to Guillermo|last=|first=|date=June 3, 2016|website=Hollywood Reporter|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jimmy-kimmel-spelling-bee-competition-899263}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.etonline.com/tv/190211_jimmy_kimmel_hilariously_challenges_spelling_bee_co_champions_to_an_epic_showdown|title=Jimmy Kimmel Hilariously Challenges Spelling Bee Co-Champions to an Epic Showdown|last=Seemayer|first=Zach|date=June 3, 2016|website=ETOnline|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://www.etonline.com/tv/190211_jimmy_kimmel_hilariously_challenges_spelling_bee_co_champions_to_an_epic_showdown}}</ref> and ''The Preachers''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jXSMJuTM_bE|title=TV Show {{!}} Spelling bee {{!}} The Preachers FOX TV SHOW 2016|last=|first=|date=2016-07-11|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> in 2016. He also appeared as a guest on the [[Harry (talk show)|''Harry'']] show in 2017.<ref>{{Citation|last=Connick Jr.|first=Harry|title=Harry's Spelling Bee Competition|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3iqBk48kKCs|volume=|pages=|language=en|access-date=2019-12-08}}</ref> Akash was interviewed on Australia\u2019s ''[[The Morning Show (TV program)|The Morning Show]]'' of [[Seven Network]] in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://7news.com.au/the-morning-show/akash-vukoti-is-the-youngest-competitor-ever-at-the-scripps-national-spelling-bee-c-198550|title=Akash Vukoti is the youngest competitor ever at the Scripps National Spelling Bee|last=|first=|date=July 3, 2019|website=7news.com.au|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://7news.com.au/the-morning-show/akash-vukoti-is-the-youngest-competitor-ever-at-the-scripps-national-spelling-bee-c-198550}}</ref> On September 25, 2018, Akash was announced as one of the celebrities who would compete on ''[[Dancing with the Stars: Juniors]],''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abc.com/shows/dancing-with-the-stars-juniors/cast/akash-vukoti|title=Akash Vukoti - Dancing with the Stars|last=|first=|date=|website=abc.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://abc.com/shows/dancing-with-the-stars-juniors/cast/akash-vukoti}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gosanangelo.com/story/entertainment/2018/12/10/san-angelo-dancing-stars-juniors-spelling-bee-legend-akash-vukoti/2241730002/|title=San Angelo whiz kid Akash Vukoti talks Dancing with the Stars and future plans|last=Sutton|first=Samuel|date=December 10, 2018|website=gosanangelo.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-08}}</ref> a spin-off of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (American TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]].'' His professional partner was Kamri Peterson and the couple were mentored by [[Witney Carson]]. The trio were eliminated 7th from the competition on November 18th, 2018.\n\n== Documentaries and films ==\nAkash has been featured in [[HBO]] and [[BBC]] documentaries. Episode 231 of ''[[Real Sports with Bryant Gumbel]]'' titled \u201cBrain Games and Mental Athletes\u201d featured Akash and aired on June 21, 2016 on HBO.<ref>{{Citation|title=Brain Games & Mental Athletes: Real Sports Trailer (HBO)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dEwAgs_nHDM|language=en|access-date=2019-12-08}}</ref> The BBC documentary ''The Human Body: Secrets of Your Life Revealed'' showcased Akash's talent in the episode \"Learn\" and aired on October 9, 2017 on [[BBC Two]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p05g7bbt/p05g7g87|title=The Human Body: Secrets of Your Life Revealed - Gallery|last=|first=|date=|website=BBC Documentary|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p05g7bbt/p05g7g87}}</ref>\n\nAkash was featured in the award winning documentary film [https://www.netflix.com/title/81069312 Spelling The Dream]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.conchovalleyhomepage.com/news/netflix-to-release-documentary-featuring-san-angelo-native-akash-vukoti/|title=Netflix to release documentary featuring San Angelo native, Akash Vukoti|date=2020-03-27|website=ConchoValleyHomepage.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Breaking The Bee |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt6193522/ |website=IMDB |ref=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt6193522/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://clevelandmagazine.com/entertainment/film-tv/articles/breaking-the-bee-examines-what-it-takes-to-w-i-n|title=What It Takes to W-I-N|last=Goodrich|first=Barry|date=April 3, 2018|website=clevelandmagazine.com/|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://clevelandmagazine.com/entertainment/film-tv/articles/breaking-the-bee-examines-what-it-takes-to-w-i-n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clevelandfilm.org/films/2018/breaking-the-bee|title=Breaking The Bee|last=|first=|date=|website=clevelandfilm.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://www.clevelandfilm.org/films/2018/breaking-the-bee}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/world-news/breaking-the-bee-indian-kids-are-spelling-out-a-new-sport-in-america/story-bUL6pxZQCDTNfrHOz0nnkK.html|title=Breaking the bee:\u2009Indian kids are spelling out a new sport in America|last=Raj|first=Yashwant|date=May 27, 2018|website=Hindustan Times|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://www.hindustantimes.com/world-news/breaking-the-bee-indian-kids-are-spelling-out-a-new-sport-in-america/story-bUL6pxZQCDTNfrHOz0nnkK.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://filmdaily.co/craft/breaking-the-bee-indian-american-dynasty/|title=Breaking the Bee: How a 20-year Indian-American dynasty was captured on film|last=Webb|first=Daisy|date=|website=filmdaily.co|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|ref=https://filmdaily.co/craft/breaking-the-bee-indian-american-dynasty/}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://spellingthedream.com/|title=Spelling the Dream|last=|first=|date=|website=Spelling the Dream|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> that is scheduled to release on Netflix on May 23, 2020.\n\n== Awards ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!YEAR\n!ASSOCIATION\n!AWARD\n!CATEGORY\n!REF.\n|-\n|2017\n|[[Telugu Association of North America]]\n|Special Recognition Award\n|Spelling & Language\n|<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1vl0DhOYP5jvvotY3EUGf6yL5QbnWfn2i/view?usp=sharing|title=TANA Patrika - January 2018|last=|first=|date=|website=drive.google.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n|-\n|2017\n|[https://www.natsworld.org/ North America Telugu Society]\n|Honorary Title\n|Dhaarana Vaamana\n|<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/125ngxoQZ5mdBW5ri6Chjnb9tRhbVO_zk/view?usp=sharing|title=NATS Akshara Deepika - June 2017|last=|first=|date=|website=drive.google.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n|-\n|2020\n|[https://www.gcpawards.com/ Global Child Prodigy Awards]\n|Global Child Prodigy Award 2020\n|Language\n|<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Rathore|first=Reena|date=|title=Young Indian American Geniuses Honored with \u20182020 Global Child Prodigy Awards\u2019|url=https://www.indiawest.com/news/global_indian/young-indian-american-geniuses-honored-with-global-child-prodigy-awards/article_f6c42cd6-3958-11ea-b32c-fb448d53cad5.html|journal=India West|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thelogicalindian.com/story-feed/get-inspired/kits-global-child-prodigy-awards/|title=KIIT Presents Global Child Prodigy Awards 2020 Honoring Top 100 Prodigies|last=Jha|first=Ankur Kumar|date=2019-12-31|website=thelogicalindian.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Personal Life ==\nAkash Vukoti is the son of Chandrakala Jandyam and Dr. Krishna M Vukoti, who immigrated to the United States from Andhra Pradesh, India. Akash has an older sister Amrita, who is also a Davidson Young Scholar and a member of Mensa.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cantonrep.com/article/20150331/NEWS/150339817|title=Weir, Kelli (April 1, 2015). \"G-E-N-I-U-S: Jackson Township siblings are among youngest Mensa members\". Canton Rep|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> She has also competed in the 2019 Scripps National Spelling Bee.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://secure.spellingbee.com/public/results/2019/round_results/speller/468|title=2019 Scripps National Spelling Bee Round by Round Results|date=|work=|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=|title=Word Whiz Kids Tap Memory Tricks at Spelling Bee|url=https://www.voanews.com/arts-culture/word-whiz-kids-tap-memory-tricks-spelling-bee|journal=|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vukoti, Akash}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Proud bhartiya", "label": "safe", "comment": "correction in Awards category", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Akash_Vukoti"}
{"title_page": "Fortunate Son (The Sopranos)", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=March 2018}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:Fortunate Son (''The Sopranos'')}}\n{{Infobox television episode\n| title          = Fortunate Son\n| series         = [[The Sopranos]]\n| caption        = Tony congratulates AJ after his football game.\n| season         = 3\n| episode        = 3\n| guests         = ''see below''\n| airdate        = March 11, 2001\n| length         = 58 minutes\n| editor         = \n| production     = 303\n| writer         = [[Todd A. Kessler]]\n| director       = [[Henry J. Bronchtein]]\n| photographer   = [[Alik Sakharov]]\n| episode_list   = List of The Sopranos episodes\n| season_article = The Sopranos (season 3)\n| image          = TheSopranosFortunateSon.jpg\n| image_size     = 300px\n| prev           = [[Proshai, Livushka]]\n| next           = [[Employee of the Month (The Sopranos)|Employee of the Month]]\n}}\n\n\"'''Fortunate Son'''\" is the 29th episode of the [[HBO]] original series ''[[The Sopranos]]'' and the third of the show's third season. It was written by [[Todd A. Kessler]] and directed by [[Henry J. Bronchtein]], and originally aired on March 11, 2001.\n\n==Starring==\n* [[James Gandolfini]] as [[Tony Soprano]]\n* [[Lorraine Bracco]] as [[Dr. Jennifer Melfi]] \n* [[Edie Falco]] as [[Carmela Soprano]]\n* [[Michael Imperioli]] as [[Christopher Moltisanti]]\n* [[Dominic Chianese]] as [[Junior Soprano|Corrado Soprano, Jr.]]\n* [[Steven Van Zandt]] as [[Silvio Dante]]\n* [[Tony Sirico]] as [[Paulie Gualtieri]]\n* [[Robert Iler]] as [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.]] \n* [[Jamie-Lynn Sigler]] as [[Meadow Soprano]]\n* [[Drea de Matteo]] as [[Adriana La Cerva]]\n* [[Aida Turturro]] as [[Janice Soprano]]\n* [[John Ventimiglia]] as [[Artie Bucco]]\n* [[Steven R. Schirripa]] as [[Bobby Baccalieri]]\n* [[Federico Castelluccio]] as [[Furio Giunta]]\n* [[Robert Funaro]] as [[Eugene Pontecorvo]]\n* [[Joe Pantoliano]] as [[Ralph Cifaretto]]\n\n===Guest starring===\n{{Columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Joseph Siravo]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#John Francis \"Johnny Boy\" Soprano|Johnny Boy Soprano]]\n* [[Rocco Sisto]] as [[Junior Soprano|Young Junior Soprano]]\n* Andrew Davoli as [[Dino Zerilli]]\n* [[Tom Aldredge]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Hugh DeAngelis|Hugh DeAngelis]]\n* [[Suzanne Shepherd]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Mary DeAngelis|Mary DeAngelis]]\n* [[Alla Kliouka Schaffer|Alla Kliouka]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Svetlana Kirilenko|Svetlana Kirilenko]]\n* [[Vincent Curatola]] as [[Johnny Sack]]\n* John Fiore as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Gigi Cestone|Gigi Cestone]]\n* [[Dan Grimaldi]] as [[Patsy Parisi]]\n* George Loros as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Raymond Curto|Raymond Curto]]\n* [[Max Casella]] as [[Benny Fazio]]\n* [[Jason Cerbone]] as [[Jackie Aprile, Jr.]]\n* [[Tony Lip]] as [[Carmine Lupertazzi]]\n* Richard Maldone as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Albert Barese|Albert Barese]]\n* [[Sharon Angela]] as [[Rosalie Aprile]]\n* [[Oksana Lada|Oksana Babiy]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Irina Peltsin|Irina Peltsin]]\n* [[Laila Robins]] as [[Livia Soprano|Young Livia Soprano]]\n* Patrick Tully as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Noah Tannenbaum|Noah Tannenbaum]]\n* Peter Byrne as Security Guard\n* Megan Curry as Punked-Out Coed\n* [[The Howard Stern Show staff#Steve Grillo|Steve Grillo]] as Pizza Customer\n* Kevin Janicelli as Roy DelGuercio\n* [[Mario Lavandeira]] as Male Student\n* [[Stephen Mellor (actor)|Steve Mellor]] as Bill Owens\n* David Mogentale as Coach Goodwin\n* Peter Napoliello as Football Dad\n* Sal Petraccione as George Piocosta\n* Frank Savino as Operator #1\n* Paul Reggio as Operator #2\n* Jessica Ripton as Pizza Customer #2\n* Johnny Spanish as Junkie\n* [[Brian Anthony Wilson]] as Warren Dupree\n* Lou Bonacki as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - friends and family#Francis Satriale|Francis Satriale]]\n* Mark Damiano II as [[Tony Soprano|Young Tony Soprano]]\n* Juliet Fox as [[Janice Soprano|Young Janice Soprano]]\n* Elxis McLaren as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Barbara Soprano Giglione|Young Barbara Soprano]]\n}}\n\n==Synopsis==\n[[Christopher Moltisanti]] is initiated as a [[made man]] in a ceremony conducted by [[Tony Soprano]]. However, he sees (or imagines he sees) a [[raven]] perched at the open window, and fears it is a bad [[omen]]. At the party afterwards, [[Paulie Walnuts|Paulie]] gives Chris his [[sportsbook]], though Chris will have to give him [[Tribute|a cut of his profits]] every week. Chris soon makes some bad judgements and comes up short. Paulie is unforgiving: he warns him to pay up by the end of the week and imposes an extra payment for the delay.\n\n[[Jackie Aprile, Jr.|Jackie Jr.]] is meant to be studying Medicine at [[Rutgers University]] but is going off the rails. Tony speaks to him. Jackie shows up late and his manner is disrespectful; Tony knows that Jackie believes he had his uncle [[Richie Aprile|Richie]] killed. He denies this and says Richie was a [[informant|rat]] who is now in [[witness protection program|witness protection]]. He urges Jackie not to follow the same way of life as his father, who did not want it for his son. But Jackie says he could never make it as a doctor, or even an osteopath. Separately, Tony tells Chris not to involve Jackie in any criminal activities.\n\nHowever, needing to pay off Paulie, Chris agrees to Jackie's plan to rob a charity concert at Rutgers. He takes over and makes Jackie the getaway driver. Nervously waiting, hearing a gunshot, Jackie wets himself. Chris then gives Paulie the rest of the money. Paulie passes his own cut up to Tony, mentioning Jackie's involvement. An angered Tony tries to telephone Chris, but he ignores the call.\n\n[[Meadow Soprano|Meadow]] is getting closer to [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Noah Tannenbaum|Noah]], and continues to give Tony the silent treatment. [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.|A.J.]] becomes involved with the school [[American football|football]] team, making his father very proud, especially when he recovers a fumble at a game. But later, at football practice, when he is elevated to defensive captain and praised effusively, he passes out on the field.\n\nPutting pressure on [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Svetlana Kirilenko|Svetlana]] to give back [[Livia Soprano|Livia]]'s record collection, [[Janice Soprano|Janice]] steals her [[artificial leg]]. Tony goes to see Svetlana and meets [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Irina Peltsin|Irina]] again. He keeps his distance. He goes to the fridge and takes out some packets of sliced meat. He suddenly remembers: when he was eleven, he saw [[Johnny Boy Soprano|his father]] chop off a gambler's [[pinky finger]]\u2014it was [[List of characters from The Sopranos - friends and family#Francis Satriale|Mr Satriale]], the butcher. At dinner, his mother was excited by the fresh juicy joint of meat she had cooked, and his parents danced sensually together in front of the children. That was when he had his first panic attack. When he tells [[Jennifer Melfi|Dr Melfi]] this, she sees a connection between meat, his parents' sexuality, and his panic attacks. \"We've made real progress today,\" she says.\n\n==Title reference==\n* The title refers to the song \"[[Fortunate Son]]\" by [[Creedence Clearwater Revival]] about American youth.\n* Four young men or boys in the episode are \"fortunate sons\": the newly \"made\" Christopher; Jackie, Jr., who believes he is his father's heir; A.J., who suffers from the same panic attacks as his father; and young Tony, seen in flashback.\n\n==First appearances==\n* '''[[Carmine Lupertazzi]]:''' Boss of the Lupertazzi Crime family, one of five New York Mafia crime families. \n* '''[[Benny Fazio]]''': Associate of Christopher and member of the Soprano crew.\n* '''[[Dino Zerilli]]''': Friend of Jackie Aprile Jr. and partner in crime.\n\n==References to other media==\n* When Adriana learns that Christopher is about to be made, she becomes worried that it might be a pretext for a hit, but Christopher chides her for \"watching too many movies.\" Soon after, after arriving at the basement location of the ceremony, Silvio tells Tony that Chris was nervous during the entire ride over, and this time, Tony kids Chris as the one who's \"watching too many movies\".\n* When Tony talks with Janice in his living room, they do so while an [[E! Channel]] program looks back at the career of [[Jayne Mansfield]], circa 1954.\n* During the flashback scene in which Tony, as a boy, is speaking to his father about how he handled watching the torture of Mr. Satriale, the signature theme from ''[[The Good, the Bad and the Ugly]]'' plays on the television set.\n* When he robs the benefit concert, Christopher wears a mask from the movie ''[[Scream (1996 film)|Scream]]''.\n* Dr. Melfi and Tony discuss the famous opening scene of ''[[In Search of Lost Time|Remembrance of Things Past]]'' by [[Marcel Proust]]. \"This [[In Search of Lost Time#Homosexuality|sounds very gay]],\" Tony comments.\n\n== Music ==\n*The music that can be heard playing in the background in the first pizza parlor scene is \"[[Rock and Roll (Led Zeppelin song)|Rock and Roll]]\" by [[Led Zeppelin]]. \"Rock and Roll\"'s appearance on this ''Sopranos'' episode was the first instance in Led Zeppelin's history that one of the band's songs was licensed for a television series.<ref>{{cite book |title=The Sopranos: The Complete Book |last1=Martin |first1=Brett |date=2007-10-30 |publisher=[[Time Inc.|Time]] |location=[[New York City|New York]] |isbn=978-1-933821-18-4 |chapter=\"This Thing of Ours\": Creating ''The Sopranos'' Universe |page=169}}</ref>\n*The music that can be heard playing in the background in the second pizza parlor scene is \"[[Ain't Talkin' 'bout Love]]\" by [[Van Halen]].\n*The music being played in the bar while the game is on is \"All Good?\" by [[De La Soul]].\n*The song played at Christopher's party at the Bada Bing is \"I See You Baby\" by [[Groove Armada]].\n*The song being played as background music in the restaurant when Tony meets Jackie Aprile, Jr. is \"[[The Happy Organ]]\" by [[Dave \"Baby\" Cortez]].\n*The next song is \"[[Sally Go 'Round the Roses]]\" by [[The Jaynetts]].\n*The song being played as background music in the scene when young Tony talks with his father is the [[Hugo Montenegro]] arrangement of [[Ennio Morricone]]s main title theme from ''[[The Good, the Bad and the Ugly]]''.\n*The song played over the end credits is \"Where's the Money\" by [[Dan Hicks (singer)|Dan Hicks]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.hbo.com/the-sopranos/episodes/3/29-fortunate-son/index.html \"Fortunate Son\"] at [[HBO]]\n*{{imdb episode|0705246|Fortunate Son}}\n*{{tv.com episode|the-sopranos/fortunate-son-46362|Fortunate Son}}\n\n{{The Sopranos}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fortunate Son}}\n[[Category:The Sopranos (season 3) episodes]]\n[[Category:2001 American television episodes]]\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=March 2018}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:Fortunate Son (''The Sopranos'')}}\n{{Infobox television episode\n| title = Fortunate Son\n| series = [[The Sopranos]]\n| season = 3\n| episode = 3\n| guests= ''see below''\n| airdate = March 11, 2001\n| length = 58 minutes\n| production = 303\n| writer = [[Todd A. Kessler]]\n| director = [[Henry J. Bronchtein]]\n| photographer = [[Alik Sakharov]]\n| episode_list = List of The Sopranos episodes\n| season_article = The Sopranos (season 3)\n| image = TheSopranosFortunateSon.jpg\n| image_size = 300px\n| prev = [[Proshai, Livushka]]\n| next = [[Employee of the Month (The Sopranos)|Employee of the Month]]\n}}\n\n\"'''Fortunate Son'''\" is the 29th episode of the [[HBO]] original series ''[[The Sopranos]]'' and the third of the show's third season. It was written by [[Todd A. Kessler]] and directed by [[Henry J. Bronchtein]], and originally aired on March 11, 2001.\n\n==Starring==\n* [[James Gandolfini]] as [[Tony Soprano]]\n* [[Lorraine Bracco]] as [[Dr. Jennifer Melfi]] \n* [[Edie Falco]] as [[Carmela Soprano]]\n* [[Michael Imperioli]] as [[Christopher Moltisanti]]\n* [[Dominic Chianese]] as [[Junior Soprano|Corrado Soprano, Jr.]]\n* [[Steven Van Zandt]] as [[Silvio Dante]]\n* [[Tony Sirico]] as [[Paulie Gualtieri]]\n* [[Robert Iler]] as [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.]] \n* [[Jamie-Lynn Sigler]] as [[Meadow Soprano]]\n* [[Drea de Matteo]] as [[Adriana La Cerva]]\n* [[Aida Turturro]] as [[Janice Soprano]]\n* [[John Ventimiglia]] as [[Artie Bucco]]\n* [[Steven R. Schirripa]] as [[Bobby Baccalieri]]\n* [[Federico Castelluccio]] as [[Furio Giunta]]\n* [[Robert Funaro]] as [[Eugene Pontecorvo]]\n* [[Joe Pantoliano]] as [[Ralph Cifaretto]]\n\n===Guest starring===\n{{Columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Joseph Siravo]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#John Francis \"Johnny Boy\" Soprano|Johnny Boy Soprano]]\n* [[Rocco Sisto]] as [[Junior Soprano|Young Junior Soprano]]\n* Andrew Davoli as [[Dino Zerilli]]\n* [[Tom Aldredge]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Hugh DeAngelis|Hugh DeAngelis]]\n* [[Suzanne Shepherd]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Mary DeAngelis|Mary DeAngelis]]\n* [[Alla Kliouka Schaffer|Alla Kliouka]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Svetlana Kirilenko|Svetlana Kirilenko]]\n* [[Vincent Curatola]] as [[Johnny Sack]]\n* John Fiore as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Gigi Cestone|Gigi Cestone]]\n* [[Dan Grimaldi]] as [[Patsy Parisi]]\n* George Loros as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Raymond Curto|Raymond Curto]]\n* [[Max Casella]] as [[Benny Fazio]]\n* [[Jason Cerbone]] as [[Jackie Aprile, Jr.]]\n* [[Tony Lip]] as [[Carmine Lupertazzi]]\n* Richard Maldone as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Albert Barese|Albert Barese]]\n* [[Sharon Angela]] as [[Rosalie Aprile]]\n* [[Oksana Lada|Oksana Babiy]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Irina Peltsin|Irina Peltsin]]\n* [[Laila Robins]] as [[Livia Soprano|Young Livia Soprano]]\n* Patrick Tully as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Noah Tannenbaum|Noah Tannenbaum]]\n* Peter Byrne as Security Guard\n* Megan Curry as Punked-Out Coed\n* [[The Howard Stern Show staff#Steve Grillo|Steve Grillo]] as Pizza Customer\n* Kevin Janicelli as Roy DelGuercio\n* [[Mario Lavandeira]] as Male Student\n* [[Stephen Mellor (actor)|Steve Mellor]] as Bill Owens\n* David Mogentale as Coach Goodwin\n* Peter Napoliello as Football Dad\n* Sal Petraccione as George Piocosta\n* Frank Savino as Operator #1\n* Paul Reggio as Operator #2\n* Jessica Ripton as Pizza Customer #2\n* Johnny Spanish as Junkie\n* [[Brian Anthony Wilson]] as Warren Dupree\n* Lou Bonacki as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - friends and family#Francis Satriale|Francis Satriale]]\n* Mark Damiano II as [[Tony Soprano|Young Tony Soprano]]\n* Juliet Fox as [[Janice Soprano|Young Janice Soprano]]\n* Elxis McLaren as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Barbara Soprano Giglione|Young Barbara Soprano]]\n}}\n\n==Synopsis==\n[[Christopher Moltisanti]] is initiated as a [[made man]] in a ceremony conducted by [[Tony Soprano]]. However, he sees (or imagines he sees) a [[raven]] perched at the open window, and fears it is a bad [[omen]]. At the party afterwards, [[Paulie Walnuts|Paulie]] gives Chris his [[sportsbook]], though Chris will have to give him [[Tribute|a cut of his profits]] every week. Chris soon makes some bad judgements and comes up short. Paulie is unforgiving: he warns him to pay up by the end of the week and imposes an extra payment for the delay.\n\n[[Jackie Aprile, Jr.|Jackie Jr.]] is meant to be studying Medicine at [[Rutgers University]] but is going off the rails. Tony speaks to him. Jackie shows up late and his manner is disrespectful; Tony knows that Jackie believes he had his uncle [[Richie Aprile|Richie]] killed. He denies this and says Richie was a [[informant|rat]] who is now in [[witness protection program|witness protection]]. He urges Jackie not to follow the same way of life as his father, who did not want it for his son. But Jackie says he could never make it as a doctor, or even an osteopath. Separately, Tony tells Chris not to involve Jackie in any criminal activities.\n\nHowever, needing to pay off Paulie, Chris agrees to Jackie's plan to rob a charity concert at Rutgers. He takes over and makes Jackie the getaway driver. Nervously waiting, hearing a gunshot, Jackie wets himself. Chris then gives Paulie the rest of the money. Paulie passes his own cut up to Tony, mentioning Jackie's involvement. An angered Tony tries to telephone Chris, but he ignores the call.\n\n[[Meadow Soprano|Meadow]] is getting closer to [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Noah Tannenbaum|Noah]], and continues to give Tony the silent treatment. [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.|A.J.]] becomes involved with the school [[American football|football]] team, making his father very proud, especially when he recovers a fumble at a game. But later, at football practice, when he is elevated to defensive captain and praised effusively, he passes out on the field.\n\nPutting pressure on [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Svetlana Kirilenko|Svetlana]] to give back [[Livia Soprano|Livia]]'s record collection, [[Janice Soprano|Janice]] steals her [[artificial leg]]. Tony goes to see Svetlana and meets [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Irina Peltsin|Irina]] again. He keeps his distance. He goes to the fridge and takes out some packets of sliced meat. He suddenly remembers: when he was eleven, he saw [[Johnny Boy Soprano|his father]] chop off a gambler's [[pinky finger]]\u2014it was [[List of characters from The Sopranos - friends and family#Francis Satriale|Mr Satriale]], the butcher. At dinner, his mother was excited by the fresh juicy joint of meat she had cooked, and his parents danced sensually together in front of the children. That was when he had his first panic attack. When he tells [[Jennifer Melfi|Dr Melfi]] this, she sees a connection between meat, his parents' sexuality, and his panic attacks. \"We've made real progress today,\" she says.\n\n==Title reference==\n* The title refers to the song \"[[Fortunate Son]]\" by [[Creedence Clearwater Revival]] about American youth.\n* Four young men or boys in the episode are \"fortunate sons\": the newly \"made\" Christopher; Jackie, Jr., who believes he is his father's heir; A.J., who suffers from the same panic attacks as his father; and young Tony, seen in flashback.\n\n==First appearances==\n* '''[[Carmine Lupertazzi]]:''' Boss of the Lupertazzi Crime family, one of five New York Mafia crime families. \n* '''[[Benny Fazio]]''': Associate of Christopher and member of the Soprano crew.\n* '''[[Dino Zerilli]]''': Friend of Jackie Aprile Jr. and partner in crime.\n\n==References to other media==\n* When Adriana learns that Christopher is about to be made, she becomes worried that it might be a pretext for a hit, but Christopher chides her for \"watching too many movies.\" Soon after, after arriving at the basement location of the ceremony, Silvio tells Tony that Chris was nervous during the entire ride over, and this time, Tony kids Chris as the one who's \"watching too many movies\".\n* When Tony talks with Janice in his living room, they do so while an [[E! Channel]] program looks back at the career of [[Jayne Mansfield]], circa 1954.\n* During the flashback scene in which Tony, as a boy, is speaking to his father about how he handled watching the torture of Mr. Satriale, the signature theme from ''[[The Good, the Bad and the Ugly]]'' plays on the television set.\n* When he robs the benefit concert, Christopher wears a mask from the movie ''[[Scream (1996 film)|Scream]]''.\n* Dr. Melfi and Tony discuss the famous opening scene of ''[[In Search of Lost Time|Remembrance of Things Past]]'' by [[Marcel Proust]]. \"This [[In Search of Lost Time#Homosexuality|sounds very gay]],\" Tony comments.\n\n== Music ==\n*The music that can be heard playing in the background in the first pizza parlor scene is \"[[Rock and Roll (Led Zeppelin song)|Rock and Roll]]\" by [[Led Zeppelin]]. \"Rock and Roll\"'s appearance on this ''Sopranos'' episode was the first instance in Led Zeppelin's history that one of the band's songs was licensed for a television series.<ref>{{cite book |title=The Sopranos: The Complete Book |last1=Martin |first1=Brett |date=2007-10-30 |publisher=[[Time Inc.|Time]] |location=[[New York City|New York]] |isbn=978-1-933821-18-4 |chapter=\"This Thing of Ours\": Creating ''The Sopranos'' Universe |page=169}}</ref>\n*The music that can be heard playing in the background in the second pizza parlor scene is \"[[Ain't Talkin' 'bout Love]]\" by [[Van Halen]].\n*The music being played in the bar while the game is on is \"All Good?\" by [[De La Soul]].\n*The song played at Christopher's party at the Bada Bing is \"I See You Baby\" by [[Groove Armada]].\n*The song being played as background music in the restaurant when Tony meets Jackie Aprile, Jr. is \"[[The Happy Organ]]\" by [[Dave \"Baby\" Cortez]].\n*The next song is \"[[Sally Go 'Round the Roses]]\" by [[The Jaynetts]].\n*The song being played as background music in the scene when young Tony talks with his father is the [[Hugo Montenegro]] arrangement of [[Ennio Morricone]]s main title theme from ''[[The Good, the Bad and the Ugly]]''.\n*The song played over the end credits is \"Where's the Money\" by [[Dan Hicks (singer)|Dan Hicks]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.hbo.com/the-sopranos/episodes/3/29-fortunate-son/index.html \"Fortunate Son\"] at [[HBO]]\n*{{imdb episode|0705246|Fortunate Son}}\n*{{tv.com episode|the-sopranos/fortunate-son-46362|Fortunate Son}}\n\n{{The Sopranos}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fortunate Son}}\n[[Category:The Sopranos (season 3) episodes]]\n[[Category:2001 American television episodes]]\n", "name_user": "Fullmetal2887", "label": "safe", "comment": "image caption", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fortunate_Son_(The_Sopranos)"}
